<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Federated Graph Autoencoder for NetFlow Anomaly Detection</title>
<meta name="description" content="A graph autoencoder that learns what normal network traffic looks like and flags what it can't explain — trained together by four organisations without sharing a single traffic record.">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Space+Grotesk:wght@400;500;600;700&family=IBM+Plex+Sans:ital,wght@0,400;0,500;0,600;1,400&family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  :root{
    --paper:#F5F7FB;
    --paper-2:#EDF1F8;
    --card:#FFFFFF;
    --ink:#0F1830;
    --ink-2:#38445F;
    --muted:#697691;
    --line:#DCE3EF;
    --hero-1:#080d1f;
    --hero-2:#0f1b3e;
    --hero-3:#132a54;
    --signal:#1BA5C4;      /* benign flow / primary in light */
    --signal-bright:#3FD3EE;/* benign flow on dark */
    --anomaly:#FF6B4A;      /* flagged / reconstruction-error heat */
    --anomaly-deep:#E8462A;
    --violet:#7C6BFF;       /* federated / aggregation */
    --ok:#12A36B;
    --shadow:0 1px 2px rgba(15,24,48,.04),0 8px 30px rgba(15,24,48,.07);
    --shadow-lg:0 30px 80px rgba(8,13,31,.45);
    --maxw:1120px;
  }
  *{box-sizing:border-box}
  html{scroll-behavior:smooth}
  body{
    margin:0;background:var(--paper);color:var(--ink);
    font-family:"IBM Plex Sans",system-ui,sans-serif;
    font-size:17px;line-height:1.65;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;
    text-rendering:optimizeLegibility;
  }
  a{color:inherit}
  img{max-width:100%;display:block}
  .wrap{max-width:var(--maxw);margin:0 auto;padding:0 28px}
  .mono{font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",ui-monospace,monospace}

  /* ---------- eyebrow / structural labels ---------- */
  .eyebrow{
    font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:12px;font-weight:500;
    letter-spacing:.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--signal);
    display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:.6em;
  }
  .eyebrow::before{content:"";width:26px;height:1px;background:var(--signal);opacity:.6}
  .eyebrow.on-dark{color:var(--signal-bright)}
  .eyebrow.on-dark::before{background:var(--signal-bright)}

  h1,h2,h3{font-family:"Space Grotesk",sans-serif;font-weight:600;line-height:1.08;letter-spacing:-.015em;margin:0}
  h2{font-size:clamp(28px,4.2vw,44px)}
  h3{font-size:22px;letter-spacing:-.01em}
  p{margin:0 0 1em}
  .lede{font-size:clamp(18px,2.2vw,22px);line-height:1.55;color:var(--ink-2)}

  /* ============ NAV ============ */
  nav{
    position:sticky;top:0;z-index:50;
    background:rgba(9,14,31,.72);backdrop-filter:blur(14px);
    border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08);
  }
  nav .wrap{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:22px;height:60px}
  .brand{font-family:"Space Grotesk",sans-serif;font-weight:600;color:#fff;font-size:15px;letter-spacing:-.01em;white-space:nowrap}
  .brand span{color:var(--signal-bright)}
  .navlinks{margin-left:auto;display:flex;gap:26px;align-items:center}
  .navlinks a{font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:12.5px;letter-spacing:.04em;color:#aab6d4;text-decoration:none;transition:color .18s}
  .navlinks a:hover{color:#fff}
  .navlinks .gh{color:#fff;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.22);padding:6px 13px;border-radius:7px}
  .navlinks .gh:hover{border-color:var(--signal-bright);background:rgba(63,211,238,.08)}
  @media(max-width:720px){.navlinks a:not(.gh){display:none}}

  /* ============ HERO ============ */
  .hero{
    position:relative;overflow:hidden;color:#eaf0ff;
    background:
      radial-gradient(1200px 600px at 78% -10%,rgba(63,211,238,.16),transparent 60%),
      radial-gradient(900px 700px at 12% 110%,rgba(124,107,255,.16),transparent 55%),
      linear-gradient(160deg,var(--hero-1),var(--hero-2) 60%,var(--hero-3));
  }
  #flowcanvas{position:absolute;inset:0;width:100%;height:100%;display:block;opacity:.9}
  .hero-grid{position:absolute;inset:0;background-image:linear-gradient(rgba(255,255,255,.035) 1px,transparent 1px),linear-gradient(90deg,rgba(255,255,255,.035) 1px,transparent 1px);background-size:52px 52px;mask-image:radial-gradient(circle at 50% 35%,#000,transparent 78%)}
  .hero .wrap{position:relative;z-index:2;padding:74px 28px 78px;min-height:min(90vh,760px);display:flex;flex-direction:column;justify-content:center}
  .hero h1{
    font-size:clamp(34px,6.2vw,68px);font-weight:600;color:#fff;
    letter-spacing:-.025em;line-height:1.02;max-width:16ch;margin:22px 0 0;
  }
  .hero h1 .hl{
    background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--signal-bright),#9fe9f6);
    -webkit-background-clip:text;background-clip:text;color:transparent;
  }
  .hero .sub{max-width:60ch;margin:24px 0 0;font-size:clamp(16px,2vw,20px);color:#b9c6e6;line-height:1.55}
  .hero .anom-word{color:var(--anomaly);font-weight:500}
  .cta-row{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:14px;margin-top:34px}
  .btn{
    font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:13.5px;letter-spacing:.02em;
    text-decoration:none;padding:12px 20px;border-radius:9px;display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:9px;
    transition:transform .16s ease,box-shadow .16s ease,background .16s;font-weight:500;
  }
  .btn-primary{background:var(--signal-bright);color:#062028;font-weight:600}
  .btn-primary:hover{transform:translateY(-2px);box-shadow:0 10px 26px rgba(63,211,238,.35)}
  .btn-ghost{color:#dfe7fb;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.2)}
  .btn-ghost:hover{border-color:#fff;transform:translateY(-2px)}

  /* metric strip */
  .metrics{
    position:relative;z-index:2;
    border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.1);
    background:linear-gradient(180deg,rgba(255,255,255,.02),rgba(255,255,255,0));
  }
  .metrics .wrap{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:0;min-height:0;padding:0 28px}
  .metric{padding:22px 26px 24px;border-left:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08)}
  .metric:first-child{border-left:none;padding-left:0}
  .metric .v{font-family:"Space Grotesk",sans-serif;font-size:clamp(26px,3.4vw,36px);font-weight:600;color:#fff;letter-spacing:-.02em;line-height:1}
  .metric .v small{font-size:.5em;color:var(--signal-bright);font-weight:500;margin-left:2px}
  .metric .k{font-family:"IBM Plex Sans",sans-serif;font-size:14px;line-height:1.4;letter-spacing:0;color:#aebcda;margin-top:11px}
  .metric .k b{color:#e7eeff;font-weight:600}
  @media(max-width:760px){.metrics .wrap{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr)}.metric{border-left:none;padding:20px 0}.metric:nth-child(odd){padding-right:20px}.metric:nth-child(even){border-left:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08);padding-left:22px}}

  /* ============ SECTIONS ============ */
  section{padding:88px 0;scroll-margin-top:72px}
  .section-head{max-width:70ch;margin-bottom:44px}
  .section-head h2{margin-top:16px}
  .section-head p{margin-top:16px}
  .alt{background:
      linear-gradient(180deg,var(--paper-2),var(--paper) 40%);
  }
  .rule{height:1px;background:var(--line);border:0;margin:0}

  /* problem cards */
  .cols3{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:20px}
  @media(max-width:820px){.cols3{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
  .cols4{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:20px}
  @media(max-width:820px){.cols4{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
  .card{
    background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:16px;padding:26px 24px;
    box-shadow:var(--shadow);
  }
  .card .tag{font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted)}
  .card h3{margin:14px 0 10px;font-size:19px}
  .card p{font-size:15.5px;color:var(--ink-2);margin:0}
  .card .ic{width:38px;height:38px;border-radius:10px;display:grid;place-items:center;font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-weight:600;font-size:16px}

  /* figure card */
  figure{margin:0}
  .fig{
    background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:16px;
    box-shadow:var(--shadow);overflow:hidden;
  }
  .fig .fig-body{padding:22px}
  .fig img{margin:0 auto;border-radius:6px}
  .fig figcaption{
    border-top:1px solid var(--line);padding:14px 20px;
    font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:12.5px;color:var(--muted);
    display:flex;gap:12px;align-items:baseline;
  }
  .fig figcaption b{color:var(--signal);font-weight:600;white-space:nowrap}
  .fig-wide{grid-column:1/-1}

  /* pipeline stage navigation */
  .stage-nav{
    position:absolute;top:42%;transform:translateY(-50%);z-index:6;width:44px;height:44px;border-radius:50%;
    border:1px solid var(--line);background:rgba(255,255,255,.94);box-shadow:var(--shadow);cursor:pointer;
    font-size:17px;color:var(--ink-2);display:grid;place-items:center;
    transition:border-color .15s,color .15s,background .15s;
  }
  .stage-nav:hover{border-color:var(--signal);color:var(--signal)}
  .stage-nav.prev{left:14px}.stage-nav.next{right:14px}
  .stage-dots{margin-left:auto;display:flex;gap:8px;align-items:center;flex:none;align-self:center}
  .stage-dots button{width:10px;height:10px;border-radius:50%;border:0;background:#c9d3e4;cursor:pointer;padding:0;transition:background .2s,transform .2s}
  .stage-dots button.on{background:var(--signal);transform:scale(1.3)}
  .stage-cap .capbody{flex:1}
  .stage-cap .capbody b{color:var(--ink);font-weight:600}

  /* just seven fields */
  .f7{display:grid;grid-template-columns:.85fr 1.15fr;gap:44px;align-items:center;margin-top:56px}
  @media(max-width:900px){.f7{grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:26px}}
  .f7-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:10px}
  @media(max-width:520px){.f7-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
  .fld{display:flex;gap:12px;align-items:baseline;background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:12px;padding:11px 15px;box-shadow:var(--shadow)}
  .fld b{font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:12.5px;color:var(--signal);font-weight:600;white-space:nowrap}
  .fld span{font-size:13.5px;color:var(--ink-2);line-height:1.45}

  .two{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1.05fr .95fr;gap:44px;align-items:center}
  @media(max-width:900px){.two{grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:32px}}
  .feat{list-style:none;padding:0;margin:20px 0 0}
  .feat li{position:relative;padding:14px 0 14px 30px;border-top:1px solid var(--line);font-size:15.5px;color:var(--ink-2)}
  .feat li:first-child{border-top:none}
  .feat li::before{content:"";position:absolute;left:0;top:20px;width:10px;height:10px;border-radius:3px;background:var(--signal);transform:rotate(45deg)}
  .feat li b{color:var(--ink);font-weight:600}
  .feat li .mono{color:var(--anomaly-deep);font-size:13.5px}

  /* result narrative blocks */
  .result-block{padding:44px 0;border-top:1px solid var(--line)}
  .result-block:first-of-type{border-top:none;padding-top:8px}
  .rb-label{font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:12px;letter-spacing:.14em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;margin-bottom:16px}
  .rb-num{font-family:"Space Grotesk",sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-weight:600;color:#fff;background:var(--ink);width:30px;height:30px;border-radius:8px;display:inline-grid;place-items:center;letter-spacing:0}
  .result-block:nth-child(4) .rb-num{background:var(--signal)}
  .rb-title{font-family:"Space Grotesk",sans-serif;font-size:clamp(22px,3vw,30px);font-weight:600;letter-spacing:-.015em;max-width:22ch;margin:0 0 14px}
  .rb-text{font-size:16.5px;color:var(--ink-2);max-width:74ch;margin:0}
  .rb-text b{color:var(--ink);font-weight:600}

  /* results table */
  .tablewrap{overflow-x:auto;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:16px;box-shadow:var(--shadow);background:var(--card)}
  table{border-collapse:collapse;width:100%;min-width:560px;font-size:15px}
  th,td{padding:14px 18px;text-align:left}
  thead th{font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);font-weight:500;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line);background:var(--paper-2)}
  tbody td{border-bottom:1px solid var(--line)}
  tbody tr:last-child td{border-bottom:none}
  td.num{font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;text-align:right;font-variant-numeric:tabular-nums}
  tr.best{background:linear-gradient(90deg,rgba(27,165,196,.09),rgba(27,165,196,.02))}
  tr.best td:first-child{position:relative}
  tr.best td:first-child::before{content:"";position:absolute;left:0;top:0;bottom:0;width:3px;background:var(--signal)}
  .best-pill{font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#fff;background:var(--signal);padding:2px 7px;border-radius:20px;margin-left:8px;vertical-align:middle}
  .best-arrow-up{color:var(--ok)}
  .best-arrow-down{color:var(--signal)}

  /* datasets */
  .ds{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:14px}
  @media(max-width:820px){.ds{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr)}}
  @media(max-width:480px){.ds{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
  .dscard{background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:14px;padding:22px;box-shadow:var(--shadow)}
  .dscard .name{font-family:"Space Grotesk",sans-serif;font-weight:600;font-size:17px}
  .dscard .env{font-family:"IBM Plex Sans",sans-serif;font-size:13.5px;line-height:1.4;color:var(--ink-2);letter-spacing:0;margin-top:6px}
  .bar{height:7px;border-radius:6px;background:var(--paper-2);margin:18px 0 8px;overflow:hidden;display:flex}
  .bar .benign{background:var(--signal)}
  .bar .attack{background:var(--anomaly)}
  .dscard .split{font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:12.5px;color:var(--ink-2);display:flex;justify-content:space-between}
  .dscard .split .a{color:var(--anomaly-deep)}
  .legend{display:flex;gap:20px;margin-top:22px;font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:12px;color:var(--muted)}
  .legend span{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:7px}
  .legend i{width:11px;height:11px;border-radius:3px;display:inline-block}

  /* privacy split */
  .priv{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:20px;margin-bottom:36px}
  @media(max-width:820px){.priv{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
  .priv .card{border-top:4px solid var(--ok)}
  .priv .card.dp{border-top-color:var(--anomaly)}
  .verdict{font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:12px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.04em;padding:4px 10px;border-radius:20px;display:inline-block;margin-bottom:6px}
  .verdict.free{color:#0a6b45;background:rgba(18,163,107,.12)}
  .verdict.costly{color:var(--anomaly-deep);background:rgba(255,107,74,.12)}

  /* takeaways */
  .takeaways{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:18px}
  @media(max-width:720px){.takeaways{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
  .tk{background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:16px;padding:26px 26px 28px;box-shadow:var(--shadow);position:relative}
  .tk-n{font-family:"Space Grotesk",sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:var(--signal);letter-spacing:.05em;margin-bottom:14px}
  .tk h3{font-size:19px;margin:0 0 10px}
  .tk p{font-size:15px;color:var(--ink-2);margin:0}

  .callout{background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--line);border-left:4px solid var(--anomaly);border-radius:12px;padding:18px 22px;margin-top:26px;font-size:15px;color:var(--ink-2)}
  .callout b{color:var(--ink)}

  /* ============ INTERACTIVE FIGURES ============ */
  .viz{background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:16px;box-shadow:var(--shadow);padding:26px 26px 20px;margin-top:26px}
  .viz-head{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;align-items:center;gap:8px 14px;margin-bottom:4px}
  .viz-head h4{font-family:"Space Grotesk",sans-serif;font-size:19px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:-.01em;margin:0}
  .pill{font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.06em;padding:3px 10px;border-radius:20px;white-space:nowrap}
  .pill.good{color:#0a6b45;background:rgba(18,163,107,.12)}
  .pill.bad{color:var(--anomaly-deep);background:rgba(255,107,74,.12)}
  .viz-sub{font-size:14px;color:var(--muted);margin:0 0 18px;max-width:78ch}
  .viz .foot{border-top:1px solid var(--line);margin-top:18px;padding-top:13px;font-size:14px;color:var(--ink-2)}
  .viz .foot b{color:var(--ink)}
  .viz .foot .fl{font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--signal);margin-right:8px}
  .vleg{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:14px 20px;margin:0 0 16px;font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:12px;color:var(--ink-2)}
  .vleg i{width:10px;height:10px;border-radius:3px;display:inline-block;margin-right:7px;vertical-align:-1px}
  .vleg i.rnd{border-radius:50%}
  .vleg i.dmd{transform:rotate(45deg);border-radius:2px}
  .axisrow{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:11px;color:var(--muted);margin-top:8px}
  .score-key{background:var(--paper-2);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:12px;padding:16px 20px;font-size:14.5px;color:var(--ink-2);margin-top:22px;max-width:78ch}
  .score-key b{color:var(--ink)}

  /* dumbbell / arrow rows */
  .drow{display:grid;grid-template-columns:170px 1fr;gap:16px;align-items:center;padding:8px 0}
  .drow+.drow{border-top:1px dashed var(--line)}
  .drow.avg{background:linear-gradient(90deg,rgba(27,165,196,.05),transparent);border-radius:8px}
  .dlab{font-family:"Space Grotesk",sans-serif;font-weight:600;font-size:14.5px;text-align:right;line-height:1.25}
  .dlab small{display:block;font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:10.5px;color:var(--muted);font-weight:400;margin-top:2px}
  .dtrack{position:relative;height:52px}
  .dtrack .flip{position:absolute;top:4px;bottom:4px;border-left:2px dashed #c7d0e2}
  .dline{position:absolute;top:50%;height:3px;width:0;background:#c9d3e4;border-radius:2px;transform:translateY(-50%);transition:width 1s cubic-bezier(.22,.8,.24,1)}
  .dline.arr{background:linear-gradient(90deg,#c9d3e4,var(--violet))}
  .dline.arr::after{content:"";position:absolute;right:-2px;top:50%;transform:translateY(-50%);border-left:8px solid var(--violet);border-top:5px solid transparent;border-bottom:5px solid transparent;opacity:0;transition:opacity .3s .7s}
  .in .dline.arr::after{opacity:1}
  .pt{position:absolute;top:50%;width:14px;height:14px;border-radius:50%;transform:translate(-50%,-50%);box-shadow:0 0 0 3px var(--card);transition:left 1s cubic-bezier(.22,.8,.24,1)}
  .pt.away{background:#aab6cf}
  .pt.home{background:var(--signal)}
  .pt.newm{background:var(--violet)}
  .bench{position:absolute;top:50%;width:11px;height:11px;background:var(--ink-2);transform:translate(-50%,-50%) rotate(45deg);border-radius:2px}
  .dval{position:absolute;font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:11px;color:var(--ink-2);transform:translateX(-50%);white-space:nowrap;transition:left 1s cubic-bezier(.22,.8,.24,1)}
  .dval.up{top:0}.dval.dn{bottom:0}
  .dval.delta{color:#0a8a52;font-weight:600;opacity:0;transition:opacity .4s .8s,left 1s cubic-bezier(.22,.8,.24,1)}
  .in .dval.delta{opacity:1}
  @media(max-width:640px){.drow{grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:2px}.dlab{text-align:left}}

  /* paired bars */
  .pb-row{display:grid;grid-template-columns:170px 1fr;gap:16px;align-items:center;padding:10px 0}
  .pb-row+.pb-row{border-top:1px dashed var(--line)}
  .pb{position:relative;height:22px;background:var(--paper-2);border-radius:6px}
  .pb+.pb{margin-top:7px}
  .pb i{position:absolute;top:0;bottom:0;left:0;width:0;border-radius:6px;transition:width 1.1s cubic-bezier(.22,.8,.24,1)}
  .pb i.catch{background:var(--signal)}
  .pb i.alarm{background:var(--anomaly)}
  .pb b{position:absolute;top:50%;transform:translateY(-50%);font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:11px;font-weight:500;white-space:nowrap;transition:left 1.1s cubic-bezier(.22,.8,.24,1)}
  @media(max-width:640px){.pb-row{grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:4px}.pb-row .dlab{text-align:left}}

  /* ranked rows (with sortable metric toggle) */
  .seg{display:inline-flex;background:var(--paper-2);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:9px;padding:3px;gap:3px;margin:0 0 16px}
  .seg button{font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:12px;padding:7px 13px;border:0;background:transparent;border-radius:7px;color:var(--muted);cursor:pointer;transition:color .15s}
  .seg button.on{background:var(--card);color:var(--ink);box-shadow:var(--shadow)}
  .rrow{display:grid;grid-template-columns:minmax(150px,240px) 1fr;gap:16px;align-items:center;padding:7px 0;transition:transform .55s cubic-bezier(.22,.8,.24,1)}
  .rlab{text-align:right;font-family:"Space Grotesk",sans-serif;font-weight:600;font-size:13.5px;line-height:1.25}
  .rlab small{display:block;font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:10.5px;color:var(--muted);font-weight:400;margin-top:1px}
  .rtrack{position:relative;height:24px}
  .rbar{position:absolute;top:4px;bottom:4px;left:0;width:0;background:#c9d3e4;border-radius:5px;transition:width .9s cubic-bezier(.22,.8,.24,1)}
  .rrow.lead .rbar{background:var(--signal)}
  .rrow.worst .rbar{background:var(--anomaly)}
  .rrow.base .rbar{background:var(--violet)}
  .rval{position:absolute;top:50%;transform:translateY(-50%);font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:11.5px;color:var(--ink-2);white-space:nowrap;transition:left .9s cubic-bezier(.22,.8,.24,1)}
  .rref{position:absolute;top:-4px;bottom:-4px;border-left:2px dashed var(--ink-2);opacity:.55}
  .rref span{position:absolute;top:-2px;left:6px;font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:9.5px;color:var(--muted);white-space:nowrap}
  .whisk{position:absolute;top:50%;height:2px;background:currentColor;transform:translateY(-50%);opacity:.45}
  .whisk::before,.whisk::after{content:"";position:absolute;top:-4px;height:10px;width:2px;background:currentColor}
  .whisk::before{left:0}.whisk::after{right:0}
  .wdot{position:absolute;top:50%;width:13px;height:13px;border-radius:50%;transform:translate(-50%,-50%);background:currentColor;box-shadow:0 0 0 3px var(--card)}
  @media(max-width:640px){.rrow{grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:2px}.rlab{text-align:left}}

  /* mini delta bars (SecAgg) */
  .mini-deltas{margin-top:14px;border-top:1px dashed var(--line);padding-top:12px}
  .md-row{display:grid;grid-template-columns:64px 1fr 52px;gap:10px;align-items:center;font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:11px;color:var(--muted);padding:3px 0}
  .md-track{position:relative;height:10px;background:var(--paper-2);border-radius:5px;overflow:hidden}
  .md-fill{position:absolute;top:0;bottom:0;left:0;width:0;background:var(--ok);border-radius:5px;transition:width .9s cubic-bezier(.22,.8,.24,1)}
  .md-val{color:#0a6b45;text-align:right}

  /* pipeline interactive stage */
  .stage{position:relative;background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:16px;box-shadow:var(--shadow);overflow:hidden;margin-top:22px}
  .stage svg{display:block;width:100%;height:auto}
  .stage-cap{border-top:1px solid var(--line);padding:15px 22px;font-size:15px;color:var(--ink-2);display:flex;gap:12px;align-items:baseline;min-height:56px}
  .stage-cap .n{font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:12px;color:var(--signal);font-weight:600;white-space:nowrap}
  .pel{opacity:0;transition:opacity .55s ease}
  .pel.on{opacity:1}
  .pipe-edge{transition:stroke .5s,stroke-width .5s,opacity .55s}
  .pulse-halo{animation:halo 2.2s ease-in-out infinite}
  @keyframes halo{0%,100%{opacity:.25}50%{opacity:.7}}

  /* federated round simulator */
  .fr-controls{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:10px;align-items:center;border-top:1px solid var(--line);padding:14px 22px;background:var(--paper-2)}
  .fr-controls .lbl{font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-right:2px}
  .tgl{font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:12px;padding:7px 13px;border-radius:20px;border:1px solid var(--line);background:var(--card);color:var(--muted);cursor:pointer;transition:all .15s}
  .tgl.on{border-color:var(--violet);color:var(--violet);background:rgba(124,107,255,.08);font-weight:600}
  .playbtn{font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;padding:7px 15px;border-radius:8px;border:1px solid var(--signal);background:var(--signal);color:#fff;cursor:pointer}
  .fr-round{margin-left:auto;font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:12px;color:var(--ink-2);background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:20px;padding:6px 13px}

  /* footer */
  footer{background:linear-gradient(160deg,var(--hero-1),var(--hero-2));color:#c3cfea;padding:64px 0 40px}
  footer .wrap{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1.4fr 1fr 1fr;gap:34px}
  @media(max-width:720px){footer .wrap{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
  footer h4{font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.14em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#7b8bb3;margin:0 0 16px;font-weight:500}
  footer .ft-brand{font-family:"Space Grotesk",sans-serif;font-size:20px;color:#fff;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:-.01em}
  footer p{font-size:14.5px;color:#9fabca;margin:12px 0 0;max-width:36ch}
  footer a{color:#c3cfea;text-decoration:none;display:block;padding:5px 0;font-size:14.5px;transition:color .15s}
  footer a:hover{color:var(--signal-bright)}
  footer .fine{grid-column:1/-1;border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08);margin-top:20px;padding-top:22px;font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:12px;color:#6b7aa0;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:10px}

  /* ===== problem → solution flow map ===== */
  .probmap{position:relative;margin-top:10px}
  .ob-links{position:absolute;inset:0;width:100%;height:100%;pointer-events:none;z-index:1}
  .ob-row{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:26px;position:relative;z-index:2}
  @media(max-width:820px){.ob-row{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:24px 18px}}
  .ob{text-align:center;padding:6px 4px;cursor:default;opacity:0;transform:translateY(14px);
    transition:transform .5s cubic-bezier(.22,.8,.24,1),opacity .5s}
  .probmap.in .ob{opacity:1;transform:none}
  .probmap.in .ob:nth-child(2){transition-delay:.08s}
  .probmap.in .ob:nth-child(3){transition-delay:.16s}
  .probmap.in .ob:nth-child(4){transition-delay:.24s}
  .ob .ic{width:54px;height:54px;margin:0 auto 13px;border-radius:16px;display:grid;place-items:center;
    background:rgba(255,107,74,.1);color:var(--anomaly-deep);
    transition:background .2s,color .2s,transform .2s,box-shadow .2s}
  .ob h3{font-size:16.5px;line-height:1.25;letter-spacing:-.01em}
  .ob p{font-size:13.5px;color:var(--muted);margin:8px auto 0;max-width:24ch;line-height:1.5}
  .ob .goes{display:none;font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:10.5px;letter-spacing:.06em;margin-top:9px;font-weight:600}
  .ob[data-to="fixA"] .goes{color:var(--signal)}
  .ob[data-to="fixB"] .goes{color:var(--violet)}
  .ob.hot .ic{transform:scale(1.12);background:var(--anomaly);color:#fff;box-shadow:0 8px 22px rgba(255,107,74,.32)}

  .fix-row{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:24px;margin-top:118px;position:relative;z-index:2}
  @media(max-width:820px){.fix-row{grid-template-columns:1fr;margin-top:28px;gap:16px}}
  .fix{display:block;text-decoration:none;border-radius:18px;padding:24px 26px;position:relative;
    opacity:0;transform:translateY(14px);
    transition:transform .3s,box-shadow .3s,border-color .3s,opacity .5s}
  .probmap.in .fix{opacity:1;transform:none;transition-delay:.4s}
  .probmap.in .fix+.fix{transition-delay:.52s}
  .fix.fixA{background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(27,165,196,.1),rgba(27,165,196,.02));border:1.5px solid rgba(27,165,196,.35)}
  .fix.fixB{background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(124,107,255,.1),rgba(124,107,255,.02));border:1.5px solid rgba(124,107,255,.35)}
  .fix .fx-k{font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;font-weight:600}
  .fixA .fx-k{color:var(--signal)}.fixB .fx-k{color:var(--violet)}
  .fix h3{font-size:21px;margin:10px 0 8px}
  .fix p{font-size:14.5px;color:var(--ink-2);margin:0;max-width:46ch}
  .fix .fx-go{font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;display:inline-block;margin-top:14px;transition:transform .2s}
  .fixA .fx-go{color:var(--signal)}.fixB .fx-go{color:var(--violet)}
  .fix:hover{transform:translateY(-3px)}
  .fixA:hover,.fixA.hot{border-color:var(--signal);box-shadow:0 12px 34px rgba(27,165,196,.18)}
  .fixB:hover,.fixB.hot{border-color:var(--violet);box-shadow:0 12px 34px rgba(124,107,255,.18)}
  .fix:hover .fx-go{transform:translateX(4px)}
  @media(max-width:820px){.ob-links{display:none}.ob .goes{display:block}}
  .ps-hint{font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:11.5px;color:var(--muted);text-align:center;margin:26px 0 0;opacity:.8}
  .ps-hint b{color:var(--signal)}

  /* ===== netflow example table ===== */
  .nf-eg{margin-top:30px}
  .nf-eg .nf-cap{font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:11.5px;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin:0 0 12px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:9px}
  .nf-eg .nf-cap::before{content:"";width:22px;height:1px;background:var(--muted);opacity:.6}
  .nf-table{overflow-x:auto;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:14px;box-shadow:var(--shadow);background:var(--card)}
  .nf-table table{min-width:640px;font-size:14px}
  .nf-table th{font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:10.5px;letter-spacing:.06em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);font-weight:500;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line);background:var(--paper-2);padding:11px 16px;text-align:left;white-space:nowrap}
  .nf-table td{padding:11px 16px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line);font-family:"IBM Plex Mono",monospace;font-size:12.5px;color:var(--ink-2);white-space:nowrap}
  .nf-table tr:last-child td{border-bottom:none}
  .nf-table td.dots{color:var(--muted);letter-spacing:.15em}
  .nf-note{font-size:13.5px;color:var(--muted);margin:12px 0 0}
  .nf-note b{color:var(--ink-2);font-weight:600}

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion:reduce){*{animation:none!important;transition:none!important}html{scroll-behavior:auto}.ob,.fix{opacity:1!important;transform:none!important}}
  :focus-visible{outline:2px solid var(--signal);outline-offset:2px;border-radius:4px}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<nav>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="brand">gnn-netflow-ad<span>.</span></div>
    <div class="navlinks">
      <a href="#problem">Problem</a>
      <a href="#pipeline">Solution</a>
      <a href="#federated">Federated</a>
      <a href="#results">Results</a>
      <a href="#takeaways">Takeaways</a>
      <a class="gh" href="https://github.com/sj-c/gnn-netflow-ad" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub ↗</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</nav>

<!-- ===================== HERO ===================== -->
<header class="hero">
  <canvas id="flowcanvas" aria-hidden="true"></canvas>
  <div class="hero-grid" aria-hidden="true"></div>
  <div class="wrap">
    <h1>Stop unseen cyberattacks — <span class="hl">without sharing</span> your network data.</h1>
    <p class="sub">
      Signature-based tools only catch attacks they've already seen, so a brand-new one slips
      straight past. Learning what <em>normal</em> looks like and flagging the
      <span class="anom-word">unusual</span> works better — but no one organisation sees enough
      traffic to learn it, and that traffic is too sensitive to pool. So four organisations train
      one detector <em>together</em>, each keeping its data at home.
    </p>
    <div class="cta-row">
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="#pipeline">See the solution →</a>
      <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="#results">Jump to results</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="metrics">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="metric"><div class="v">4 <span style="color:var(--signal-bright);font-size:.6em;vertical-align:.12em">→</span> 1</div><div class="k"><b>Four organisations</b> team up on one shared detector</div></div>
      <div class="metric"><div class="v">0</div><div class="k">Traffic records they had to hand over to do it — <b>zero, ever</b></div></div>
      <div class="metric"><div class="v">78<small>%</small></div><div class="k">Of real attacks caught by the shared detector <b>· best setup</b></div></div>
      <div class="metric"><div class="v">92k<small>/sec</small></div><div class="k">Connections screened every second — <b>no fancy hardware needed</b></div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<!-- ===================== PROBLEM ===================== -->
<section id="problem">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="eyebrow">The problem</div>
      <h2>Why new attacks still slip through.</h2>
      <p class="lede">Four obstacles block the obvious approaches — and they pair up neatly with the
        two ideas this project combines.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="probmap" id="probmap">
      <svg class="ob-links" aria-hidden="true"></svg>
      <div class="ob-row">
        <div class="ob" data-to="fixA" tabindex="0">
          <div class="ic"><svg width="26" height="26" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 3l7 3v5c0 4.5-3 8-7 10-4-2-7-5.5-7-10V6z"/><path d="M10 9.3a2 2 0 1 1 2.6 1.9c-.5.2-.6.6-.6 1.1v.4"/><circle cx="12" cy="15.6" r="0.35" fill="currentColor"/></svg></div>
          <h3>No signature to match</h3>
          <p>A brand-new attack has never been seen — there's nothing to look it up against.</p>
          <div class="goes">↳ idea 1</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ob" data-to="fixA" tabindex="0">
          <div class="ic"><svg width="26" height="26" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M4 4h7l9 9-7 7-9-9z"/><circle cx="8.5" cy="8.5" r="1.4"/><path d="M4 20L20 4" opacity=".6"/></svg></div>
          <h3>Almost no labelled attacks</h3>
          <p>Real, labelled attack examples are far too rare to teach a model what "attack" looks like.</p>
          <div class="goes">↳ idea 1</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ob" data-to="fixB" tabindex="0">
          <div class="ic"><svg width="26" height="26" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M3 8c2-3.5 4 3.5 6 0s4 3.5 6 0 4 3.5 6 0"/><path d="M3 17h3l2-5 3 8 2-5h8"/></svg></div>
          <h3>Every network is different</h3>
          <p>"Normal" at a bank looks nothing like "normal" in a smart factory.</p>
          <div class="goes">↳ idea 2</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ob" data-to="fixB" tabindex="0">
          <div class="ic"><svg width="26" height="26" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="5" y="11" width="14" height="9" rx="2"/><path d="M8 11V8a4 4 0 0 1 8 0v3"/><circle cx="12" cy="15.5" r="1.2"/></svg></div>
          <h3>Traffic can't be pooled</h3>
          <p>Flow records reveal who talks to whom inside a network — no one can hand them over.</p>
          <div class="goes">↳ idea 2</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="fix-row">
        <a class="fix fixA" id="fixA" href="#pipeline">
          <span class="fx-k">Idea 1 · graph autoencoder</span>
          <h3>Study normal, flag the strange</h3>
          <p>The model trains only on everyday traffic and flags whatever doesn't fit — no signatures, no attack labels needed.</p>
          <span class="fx-go">See how it works ↓</span>
        </a>
        <a class="fix fixB" id="fixB" href="#federated">
          <span class="fx-k">Idea 2 · federated learning</span>
          <h3>Train together, keep data home</h3>
          <p>Four organisations improve one shared detector by exchanging only model updates — never a single traffic record.</p>
          <span class="fx-go">See how it works ↓</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="ps-hint">Hover an obstacle to trace <b>which idea knocks it down</b> — click an idea to jump straight to it.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===================== DATASETS ===================== -->
<section class="alt" id="datasets">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="eyebrow">The proving ground</div>
      <h2>Four very different networks.</h2>
      <p class="lede">Each record is one <b>NetFlow</b> log — who talked to whom, for how long, and how much
        data, never the contents. The detector is tested on four public NetFlow benchmarks, each standing in
        for one organisation, chosen to differ in every way that matters.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="nf-eg">
      <div class="nf-cap">What one NetFlow record looks like</div>
      <div class="nf-table">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Source</th><th>Destination</th><th>Proto</th><th>Duration</th><th>Packets</th><th>Bytes</th><th>…</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>10.0.0.14</td><td>172.16.2.9</td><td>TCP</td><td>0.42 s</td><td>12</td><td>1,004</td><td class="dots">…</td></tr>
            <tr><td>10.0.0.14</td><td>8.8.8.8</td><td>UDP</td><td>0.01 s</td><td>2</td><td>148</td><td class="dots">…</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="nf-note">Just <b>metadata about each connection</b> — no message contents. A handful of numeric
        and categorical fields per flow; the detector turns thousands of these into the graph it scores.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ds">
      <div class="dscard">
        <div class="name">NF-CSE-CIC-IDS2018</div>
        <div class="env">Large corporate network</div>
        <div class="bar"><span class="benign" style="width:87.1%"></span><span class="attack" style="width:12.9%"></span></div>
        <div class="split"><span>20.1M flows</span><span class="a">12.9% attack</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="dscard">
        <div class="name">NF-UNSW-NB15</div>
        <div class="env">Corporate network, mixed attacks</div>
        <div class="bar"><span class="benign" style="width:94.6%"></span><span class="attack" style="width:5.4%"></span></div>
        <div class="split"><span>2.4M flows</span><span class="a">5.4% attack</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="dscard">
        <div class="name">NF-ToN-IoT</div>
        <div class="env">Smart devices + office network</div>
        <div class="bar"><span class="benign" style="width:61%"></span><span class="attack" style="width:39%"></span></div>
        <div class="split"><span>27.5M flows</span><span class="a">39% attack</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="dscard">
        <div class="name">NF-BoT-IoT</div>
        <div class="env">Smart-device network under heavy attack</div>
        <div class="bar"><span class="benign" style="width:0.3%"></span><span class="attack" style="width:99.7%"></span></div>
        <div class="split"><span>17.0M flows</span><span class="a">99.7% attack</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="legend">
      <span><i style="background:var(--signal)"></i> benign flows</span>
      <span><i style="background:var(--anomaly)"></i> attack flows</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===================== PIPELINE / MODEL ===================== -->
<section id="pipeline">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="eyebrow">The model</div>
      <h2>Connection logs in, suspicion scores out.</h2>
      <p class="lede">The detector is a graph autoencoder — think of it as a very good guesser. Trained
        only on normal traffic, it covers up each connection's numbers and tries to guess them from
        the context around it. When reality lands far from its guess, it's looking at something it
        has never seen — and that connection gets flagged.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="stage" id="pipe-stage" aria-label="Animated pipeline diagram">
      <button class="stage-nav prev" id="pipe-prev" aria-label="Previous step">←</button>
      <button class="stage-nav next" id="pipe-next" aria-label="Next step">→</button>
      <svg viewBox="0 0 920 360" role="img" aria-label="Diagram showing connection records becoming a directed graph, device profiles, a network summary, guessed connection values and one flagged anomaly" id="pipe-svg"></svg>
      <div class="stage-cap">
        <span class="n" id="pipe-cap-n">STEP 1 / 5</span>
        <span class="capbody"><b id="pipe-cap-t">Draw the graph.</b> <span id="pipe-cap">Take 1,000 connection records and turn them into a directed graph — each device a dot, each connection an arrow from sender to receiver.</span></span>
        <div class="stage-dots" id="pipe-dots" aria-label="Go to step"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <noscript><figure class="fig" style="margin-top:22px"><div class="fig-body"><img src="assets/pipeline.png" alt="Graph Autoencoder pipeline diagram"></div></figure></noscript>

    <div class="f7">
      <div>
        <div class="eyebrow">What it needs</div>
        <h3 style="margin:14px 0 10px">Just seven fields per connection.</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--ink-2);font-size:15.5px;margin:0">That's the whole ingredient list — the same
          connection metadata any router already exports (the table in the section above). No message
          contents, no software installed on anyone's devices.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="f7-grid">
        <div class="fld"><b>duration</b><span>how long the connection lasted</span></div>
        <div class="fld"><b>packets</b><span>how many packets crossed</span></div>
        <div class="fld"><b>bytes</b><span>how much data moved</span></div>
        <div class="fld"><b>min TTL</b><span>a rough hint of how far away the sender is</span></div>
        <div class="fld"><b>protocol</b><span>the language spoken — TCP, UDP…</span></div>
        <div class="fld"><b>source port</b><span>which service sent it</span></div>
        <div class="fld"><b>dest port</b><span>which service it was for — web, mail, DNS…</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===================== FEDERATED ===================== -->
<section class="alt" id="federated">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="eyebrow">Federated learning</div>
      <h2>Train together. Keep your data.</h2>
      <p class="lede">Built on Flower, one client per organisation. Each round, the coordinator hands out
        one shared model, every organisation trains it on data that never leaves home, and only the model
        updates travel back. Press play — every step is explained right on the diagram, where it happens.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="stage" id="fedround">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 960 430" role="img" aria-label="Animated diagram of one federated learning round: the coordinator sends a model to four organisations, each trains on traffic logs that stay behind a fence, and only model updates — optionally masked or noised — travel back to be averaged" id="fr-svg"></svg>
      <div class="fr-controls">
        <button class="playbtn" id="fr-play" aria-pressed="false">▶ Play</button>
        <span class="lbl">Options:</span>
        <button class="tgl on" id="tg-fedbn" aria-pressed="true">Keep BN local (FedBN)</button>
        <button class="tgl" id="tg-secagg" aria-pressed="false">Mask updates (SecAgg+)</button>
        <button class="tgl" id="tg-dp" aria-pressed="false">Add noise (DP)</button>
        <span class="fr-round" id="fr-round">Round 1 of 50</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <noscript><figure class="fig fig-wide"><div class="fig-body"><img src="assets/federated-round.png" alt="One federated round, step by step"></div></figure></noscript>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===================== RESULTS ===================== -->
<section id="results">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="eyebrow">Results · the argument in four steps</div>
      <h2>What the experiments show.</h2>
      <p class="lede">The results build a case. A model trained on one network doesn't transfer. Naively pooling
        everyone's data makes it worse. Federating <em>does</em> help — but only once each client keeps its
        own normalisation. And even then, a brand-new network still needs a local touch.</p>
      <div class="score-key"><b>How to read the numbers.</b> <b>Detection score</b> runs 0–100: at 100 the
        detector ranks every attack above every normal connection; at 50 it's no better than a coin flip.
        <b>Attacks caught</b> is the share of real attacks it flags. <b>False alarms</b> is the share of
        normal traffic it wrongly flags — the number that decides whether a security team can actually live
        with the tool.</div>
    </div>

    <!-- step 1: local baselines -->
    <div class="result-block">
      <div class="rb-label"><span class="rb-num">01</span> The domain gap</div>
      <h3 class="rb-title">One model per network is strong at home, weak everywhere else.</h3>
      <p class="rb-text">Each dataset-specific detector separates attacks well on its own traffic — within-dataset
        ranking runs from 0.722 on BoT-IoT to 0.946 on CICIDS. Point the same model at another network and
        performance falls off a cliff: cross-dataset ROC-AUC averages just 0.45–0.69, several barely above a
        coin flip. The model learned each environment's quirks, not a universal notion of "normal traffic."</p>
      <div class="viz" id="viz-homeaway" data-viz>
        <div class="viz-head"><h4>Strong at home, near coin-flip away.</h4><span class="pill bad">the domain gap</span></div>
        <p class="viz-sub">Each network's own detector, tested on its own traffic (<b style="color:var(--signal)">cyan</b>)
          vs the same detector pointed at the other three networks (grey, averaged). The dashed line is a coin flip.</p>
        <div class="vleg"><span><i class="rnd" style="background:var(--signal)"></i> tested at home</span><span><i class="rnd" style="background:#aab6cf"></i> tested away (avg)</span><span><i style="background:none;border-left:2px dashed #c7d0e2;width:2px;border-radius:0"></i> coin flip (50)</span></div>
        <div class="dumb"></div>
        <div class="axisrow"><span>40</span><span>detection score</span><span>100</span></div>
        <div class="foot"><span class="fl">Takeaway</span>Every detector loses 9 to 49 points the moment it leaves home. "Normal traffic" is not one thing — each network has its own.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="viz" id="viz-caught" data-viz>
        <div class="viz-head"><h4>Catching attacks is easy. Staying quiet is hard.</h4><span class="pill bad">the false-alarm problem</span></div>
        <p class="viz-sub">The same four home detectors: how many real attacks they catch, and how much normal
          traffic they wrongly flag while doing it.</p>
        <div class="pbars"></div>
        <div class="foot"><span class="fl">Takeaway</span>BoT-IoT looks like the star — <b>96% of attacks caught</b> — until you see it also flags <b>41% of normal traffic</b>. On a real network that's thousands of false alerts a day, and the tool gets switched off.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- step 2: centralised pooling -->
    <div class="result-block">
      <div class="rb-label"><span class="rb-num">02</span> The obvious fix that fails</div>
      <h3 class="rb-title">Simply pooling all the data makes things worse.</h3>
      <p class="rb-text">The intuitive answer is to merge every dataset into one big training set. It backfires. A
        single combined model scores a macro-average ROC-AUC of ~0.734 — <em>below</em> the average of the four
        local models — and keeps high false-alarm rates on most datasets. This is negative transfer: one shared
        representation and one shared scaler blur the real differences between networks. Personalising the
        decoder or the batch-norm helps some clients but no single centralised variant wins everywhere.</p>
      <div class="viz" id="viz-central" data-viz>
        <div class="viz-head"><h4>"One big pot" comes dead last.</h4><span class="pill bad">negative transfer</span></div>
        <p class="viz-sub">Eight ways to combine four networks' data in one place, ranked. Every fix that gives each
          network back something of its own beats the fully-shared pot. Switch the ranking to see false alarms.</p>
        <div class="seg" role="tablist"><button class="on" data-metric="score">Detection score</button><button data-metric="alarms">False alarms</button></div>
        <div class="rank"></div>
        <div class="axisrow"><span>50 (coin flip)</span><span class="axcap">detection score, average of all four networks</span><span class="axmax">90</span></div>
        <div class="foot"><span class="fl">Takeaway</span>Even the <b>best</b> pooled recipe only just beats "no sharing at all" — and it needs everyone's raw data on one machine, which is exactly what privacy rules forbid. That dead end is why the project turns to federated learning.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- step 3: federated -->
    <div class="result-block">
      <div class="rb-label"><span class="rb-num">03</span> The solution that works</div>
      <h3 class="rb-title">Federate the shared parts, keep normalisation local.</h3>
      <p class="rb-text">Federated learning shares knowledge without sharing data — and the winning recipe is
        <b>FedAvg + FedBN</b>: average the network, but let each client keep its own batch-norm to absorb its
        traffic's scale. It posts the best ranking and F1 <em>and</em> the lowest false-alarm rate. Versus the
        local baselines it lifts macro ROC-AUC ~2 points and F1 ~7 points while roughly halving false alarms.
        Sharing <em>everything</em> (no personalisation) is markedly weaker, and FedProx's proximal constraint
        didn't beat plain FedAvg here.</p>

      <div class="tablewrap" style="margin-top:26px">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Aggregation / personalisation</th><th style="text-align:right">ROC-AUC ↑</th><th style="text-align:right">F1 ↑</th><th style="text-align:right">FPR ↓</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr class="best"><td>FedAvg&nbsp;/&nbsp;FedBN<span class="best-pill">best</span></td><td class="num">0.852</td><td class="num">0.831</td><td class="num">0.088</td></tr>
            <tr><td>FedProx&nbsp;/&nbsp;FedBN</td><td class="num">0.848</td><td class="num">0.817</td><td class="num">0.095</td></tr>
            <tr><td>FedProx&nbsp;/&nbsp;FedRep</td><td class="num">0.837</td><td class="num">0.796</td><td class="num">0.148</td></tr>
            <tr><td>FedAvg&nbsp;/&nbsp;FedRep</td><td class="num">0.833</td><td class="num">0.804</td><td class="num">0.148</td></tr>
            <tr><td>FedAvg&nbsp;/&nbsp;none</td><td class="num">0.818</td><td class="num">0.747</td><td class="num">0.140</td></tr>
            <tr><td>FedProx&nbsp;/&nbsp;none</td><td class="num">0.773</td><td class="num">0.733</td><td class="num">0.203</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="mono" style="font-size:12.5px;color:var(--muted);margin-top:14px">Macro-average across the four datasets, three seeds. Threshold set by Youden's J on the ROC curve.</p>

      <div class="viz" id="viz-fed" data-viz>
        <div class="viz-head"><h4>FedAvg + FedBN wins on both counts.</h4><span class="pill good">best configuration</span></div>
        <p class="viz-sub">All six federated recipes, ranked. The dot is the average over three runs; the bar shows
          run-to-run spread. The dashed marker is the best centralised recipe from the previous chart — the one that
          needed pooled raw data.</p>
        <div class="seg" role="tablist"><button class="on" data-metric="score">Detection score</button><button data-metric="alarms">False alarms</button></div>
        <div class="rank"></div>
        <div class="axisrow"><span class="axmin">72</span><span class="axcap">detection score, average of all four networks</span><span class="axmax">90</span></div>
        <div class="foot"><span class="fl">Takeaway</span>Sharing everything (plain rows) is the weakest way to federate. Let each network keep just its own <b>scaling</b> (FedBN) and the federation beats the pooled-data model — <b>without any raw data changing hands</b>, and with roughly half the false alarms.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- step 4: cross-dataset -->
    <div class="result-block">
      <div class="rb-label"><span class="rb-num">04</span> The honest caveat</div>
      <h3 class="rb-title">It transfers better to unseen networks — but not for free.</h3>
      <p class="rb-text">In a leave-one-dataset-out test, a model trained on three networks generalises to the
        held-out fourth better than any single-source transfer — for <em>all four</em> datasets. The jumps are
        largest on CICIDS (+31.6) and UNSW (+22.3), moving each point toward the same-network benchmark ceiling.
        But the gap shrinks, it doesn't close: held-out BoT-IoT and CICIDS still fire far too many false alarms.
        A new organisation joining the federation would still need local calibration before going live.</p>
      <div class="viz" id="viz-transfer" data-viz>
        <div class="viz-head"><h4>Three teachers beat one — on every new network.</h4><span class="pill good">generalisation</span></div>
        <p class="viz-sub">Each row is a network the model has <em>never seen</em>. Grey dot: taught by one other
          network. Violet dot: taught by the other three together. The arrow is the improvement; the dark diamond is
          the ceiling — a detector trained on that network's own data.</p>
        <div class="vleg"><span><i class="rnd" style="background:#aab6cf"></i> taught by 1 network</span><span><i class="rnd" style="background:var(--violet)"></i> taught by 3 networks</span><span><i class="dmd" style="background:var(--ink-2)"></i> home-trained ceiling</span></div>
        <div class="dumb"></div>
        <div class="axisrow"><span>40</span><span>detection score on the never-seen network</span><span>100</span></div>
        <div class="foot"><span class="fl">Takeaway</span>Learning from three different networks adds up to <b>+31.6 points</b> on a brand-new one — real progress toward a detector a new organisation could adopt. But the arrows never quite reach the diamonds: a newcomer still needs some local tuning before going live.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===================== PRIVACY ===================== -->
<section class="alt" id="privacy">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="eyebrow">Privacy mechanisms</div>
      <h2>Two defences, two very different price tags.</h2>
      <p class="lede">Keeping raw data local isn't automatically private — model updates leak too. The project
        adds two protections, and measures what each one costs in detection quality.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="priv">
      <div class="card">
        <span class="verdict free">≈ free</span>
        <h3>Secure aggregation · SecAgg+</h3>
        <p>Each organisation hides its update behind a secret mask before sending. The masks are built in pairs that cancel out when everything is added up — so the coordinator gets the correct <b>total</b> but can never read any single organisation's update. The maths of the average is unchanged, so detection barely moves:</p>
        <div class="mini-deltas" id="viz-secagg" data-viz aria-label="Change in detection score with secure aggregation turned on, per network"></div>
        <p style="margin:10px 0 0;font-size:13px;color:var(--muted)">Change in detection score with SecAgg+ switched on — every network stayed level or got slightly <em>better</em>. Turn it on by default.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card dp">
        <span class="verdict costly">steep trade-off</span>
        <h3>Central differential privacy</h3>
        <p>Server-side clipping (C = 0.13) plus Gaussian noise makes the released model provably insensitive to any one client. But with only four clients there's no subsampling amplification — useful utility is gone while the privacy budget ε is still in the hundreds.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="viz" id="viz-dp" data-viz>
      <div class="viz-head"><h4>Turn the privacy dial up, and detection collapses.</h4><span class="pill bad">honest negative result</span></div>
      <p class="viz-sub">Differential privacy works by adding random noise to the shared model. Each dot is one
        setting of that dial, from a whisper of noise (left) to a strong, provable privacy guarantee (right).
        Hover a dot for the exact numbers.</p>
      <div class="dp-chart"></div>
      <div class="foot"><span class="fl">Takeaway</span>The score only stays near the no-noise baseline while the added privacy is <b>cosmetic</b>. By the time the guarantee becomes mathematically meaningful (right-hand zone), the detector is a coin flip. With only four participants there's no crowd to hide in — this kind of formal privacy needs many more organisations at the table.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===================== SPEED / DEPLOY ===================== -->
<section id="speed">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="eyebrow">Deployability</div>
      <h2>Fast enough to run on commodity CPUs.</h2>
      <p class="lede">Benchmarked on the 1.22M-flow UNSW holdout. The 323K-parameter model is so light that on
        a GPU the bottleneck is building the graphs, not running the network — and even CPU-only clears
        90,000 flows per second inside 4 GB of RAM.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tablewrap">
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th style="text-align:right">GPU · A100 40GB</th><th style="text-align:right">CPU · EPYC 7352</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>End-to-end throughput</td><td class="num">270k flows/s</td><td class="num">92k flows/s</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Model-only forward pass</td><td class="num">5.66M flows/s</td><td class="num">133k flows/s</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Total time · 1.22M flows</td><td class="num">4.5 s</td><td class="num">13.2 s</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Batch latency p50 / p99</td><td class="num">37 / 71 ms</td><td class="num">1.9 / 2.2 s</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Peak memory</td><td class="num">3.0 GB + 2.6 GB VRAM</td><td class="num">3.6 GB RAM</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div class="callout">
      <b>Where the time goes.</b> On GPU, 93% of end-to-end time is CPU-side graph construction — the forward pass is 0.2 s of 4.5 s. So each participating organisation can run both training and inference without specialised accelerators.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===================== TAKEAWAYS ===================== -->
<section class="alt" id="takeaways">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="eyebrow">Takeaways</div>
      <h2>What the project establishes.</h2>
      <p class="lede">Federated personalisation can improve NetFlow anomaly detection under non-IID conditions —
        but it complements client-specific calibration rather than replacing it.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="takeaways">
      <div class="tk">
        <div class="tk-n">01</div>
        <h3>Behaviour is environment-specific</h3>
        <p>The graph autoencoder learns useful "normal traffic" within a network, but those representations transfer poorly. NetFlow is strongly local.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tk">
        <div class="tk-n">02</div>
        <h3>Share, don't pool — and keep BN local</h3>
        <p>Naive pooling and full parameter sharing underperform. FedAvg + FedBN gives the best overall balance: 0.852 ROC-AUC, 0.831 F1, 0.088 FPR.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tk">
        <div class="tk-n">03</div>
        <h3>Generalisation improves, gap remains</h3>
        <p>Multi-client training beats single-source transfer to every unseen dataset, yet held-out false-alarm rates show local calibration is still needed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tk">
        <div class="tk-n">04</div>
        <h3>Privacy depends on the threat</h3>
        <p>SecAgg+ hides individual updates for free. But at four clients, formal client-level differential privacy costs too much utility to be practical.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="cta-row" style="margin-top:38px">
      <a class="btn btn-primary" style="background:var(--signal);color:#fff" href="https://github.com/sj-c/gnn-netflow-ad" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Explore the code on GitHub ↗</a>
      <a class="btn btn-ghost" style="color:var(--ink);border-color:var(--line)" href="https://github.com/sj-c/gnn-netflow-ad/blob/main/federated/README.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Federated protocol writeup</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

